text: Hwang Eun-suk (born 14 April 1973) is a South Korean taekwondo practitioner. She won a gold medal in bantamweight at the 1997 World Taekwondo Championships in Hong Kong, by defeating Elisabet Delgado in the semifinal, and Roxane Forget in the final. ==References== ==External links== * Category:1973 births Category:Living people Category:South Korean female taekwondo practitioners Category:World Taekwondo Championships medalists
